[flake8]
# WPS412 forbids logic in an __init__.py and WPS410 forbids module-level
# metadata such as __all__. Two package initializers deliberately carry
# import-time logic and are scoped exemptions here:
#
# * orchestrator/config/__init__.py invokes the `environment` resolver and
#   binds its results so reloading or patching `orchestrator.config` re-runs
#   resolution into the same namespace the helpers read -- the reload / patch
#   contract this package exists to preserve -- and publishes its narrow
#   public surface through an explicit __all__ (WPS410) in that initializer.
# * orchestrator/agents/__init__.py is the stable agent facade: it defines the
#   subprocess-group lifecycle and binds the runner / model / environment
#   compatibility aliases so `orchestrator.agents` stays the historical import
#   and patch site. It declares no __all__, so WPS412 is waived. It also owns a
#   PEP 562 module `__getattr__` (WPS413) that resolves the session / backend /
#   runner re-exports lazily -- the retained leaves import the `models` /
#   `environment` owners directly, so binding those re-exports eagerly would
#   re-enter `_agent_api` mid-initialization. That hook is the 8th module member
#   (WPS202), and both it and `run_agent` defer their package import to call
#   time so dispatch stays patch-aware without an import-time cycle, which puts
#   the module one import past the ceiling (WPS201); all are waived here.
per-file-ignores =
    orchestrator/config/__init__.py:WPS412,WPS410
    orchestrator/agents/__init__.py:WPS412,WPS413,WPS202,WPS201
